-- SEC Sues College Football Hall of Fame Coach Over Ponzi Scheme
-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 2012-08-16T14:37:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/sec-sues-college-football-hall-of-fame-coach-over-ponzi-scheme.html
The Securities and Exchange
Commission said it sued a former college football coach who
teamed with an Ohio man to conduct an $80 million  Ponzi scheme .  The SEC claimed that Jim Donnan, former coach at Marshall
University and the University of Georgia and later a television
commentator, conducted the fraud with his business partner
Gregory Crabtree, according to an e-mailed statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  